      "role": "user",
      "content": "a \"shared, underlying system trigger\"... that's exactly what i'm worried about. like, if they're talking to each other through my network, what's the point? is it possible they're actually sending this data somewhere else? like, if they pick up on my stress, could that info be being uploaded to a server to build a profile on my behavior or something? it just feels too synced up to be a random software loop.",
