      "content": "It is entirely possible that your connected devices are gathering data, as most smart home technology utilizes cloud services to function and update. The data collected—including operational status, environmental readings, and potentially audio snippets if microphones are active—is usually transmitted to manufacturer servers. If you are concerned about profiling, check the privacy settings within the apps associated with both your thermostat and fridge to understand exactly what data is being shared and with whom. You can also try temporarily disabling cloud connectivity to see if the strange synchronization stops.",
